16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 14-115.6, as
18 last amended by Section 23, Chapter 452, O.S.L. 2024 (26 O.S. Supp.
19 2024, Section 14-115.6), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 14-115.6. A. A registered voter who, after the
21 deadline to request an absentee ballot as provided in Section 14-103
22 of this title, is deployed as either a first:
23
24
SB814 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 1. First responder or emergency worker to assist with the
2 rescue, recovery, or relief efforts of a declared natural disaster
3 or state of emergency,; or
4 2. Uniformed-service voter as defined in Section 14-137 of this
5 title,
6 may make a written request for an emergency absentee ballot in a
7 form prescribed by the Secretary of the State Election Board. The
8 request shall be signed by the voter and shall be provided by the
9 voter to the secretary of the county election board in the county
10 where the voter is registered. Requirements for matching of name,
11 birth date, and identification number established pursuant to
12 Section 14-105 of this title shall apply to a request for an
13 absentee ballot under this section.
14 B. Upon receipt of the voter’s request, the secretary of the
15 county election board shall issue to the voter the appropriate
16 ballots and envelopes required for voting an emergency absentee
17 ballot. Provided, the voter shall present proof of identity as
18 required by Section 7-114 of this title.
19 C. The ballots must be returned in person by the voter, by
20 United States mail, or by other means of delivery approved by the
21 Secretary of the State Election Board, to the secretary of the
22 county election board no later than 7:00 p.m. on the day of the
23 election.
24
SB814 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 D. Upon return of the absentee ballots, the secretary of the
2 county election board shall cause the ballots to be processed in the
3 same manner as is prescribed for other absentee ballots.
4 E. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall promulgate
5 rules to implement the procedures described in this section.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
7 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
8 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
9 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
10 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
11
